      • adddate

        public java.util.Date adddate(int day,
                              int month,
                              int year,
                              java.lang.String type)
        Add date function is used to set any given date in calender and takes string variable to indicate if user want the reservation daily or weekly or monthly and returns date.
        Parameters:
        day - An integer number of day from 1 to 31.
        month - An integer number of month from 1 to 12.
        year - An integer number of year greater than or equal 2020.
        type - A string which is daily or weekly or monthly to calculate the auto-generated-date.
        Returns:
        returns a date after setting it to a calender.
